Try to fix bug in perf mesures
Try to fix bug in perf mesures
Add immutabkle empty array/object singleton implementations see http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30730020/reactjs-how-to-use-an-immutable-empty-array-or-object
Do not try to use Perf module in production mode
Return immutable empty array singleton when possible
Add atom transaction time logging
Implement cursor memoization for render phase
Enhance cursor memoization. Add dynamic / memoized cursors semantics
Fix issue with getCreationTimeValue() because of typo
Do not log atomreact transactions that did not modify anything
enhance saga behavior of atom-react
increment version
Allow react 0.14
remove <0.15.0 boundary for react peerDependency
Try to allow usage of 0.14 beta1
Remove useless div wrapper node not required to provide react context
Rework error logging because react intl does not provide any error.stack property on SyntaxError see https://github.com/yahoo/intl-messageformat/issues/107
Minor atom-react fixes
Little fix to ease extraction of list of values from async cursors
add "isInstanceOf" method to cursor
Fix little bugs + refactor new implementation of cursor.asyncList()
Update version

Experiment with command queuing instead of using setTimeout for sagas, so that React does not render until all the queued commands are executed -> can lead to good performance gains on mobile by avoiding extra useless renderings
Fix bug in command queue flushing implementation
Fix bug in command queue flushing implementation
Allow AtomReact classes to use local state, because always rendering from the very top can sometimes cause performance problems
Do not use expensive DeepFreeze task when used in production mode + Envify setting for Browserify

Rework error handling: rethrow errors to that debugging is easier with sourcemaps, because console.error of sourcemaps is not so great with sourcemaps write now.
See https://github.com/webpack/webpack/issues/1646
Try to make sure transaction errors are always logged correctly
Use console.group when available
Deprecate command/event publishing from components and replace it with an Action api that looks closer to Flux ActionCreators. action side-effects are allowed in the stores
fail faster + typo
Do not deprecate event publishing finally
For store side-effects, the actions should be declared with prototype methods
Fix bug in getPathDiff after updating lodash
Add setAsyncSuccess to cursors
Allow to call cursor.update on undefined value
Wire actions at componentWillMount instead of DidMount
Add reduce to atomReact cursor api
Conform event attributes to flux-standard-action
add getState api on atomreact context/store
Better error logging + fail harder on app startup because if init fails most likely the app is totally unusable
Better error handling in case of listener failure
Allow actions to access context and state
Deprecate atomReact in favor of Redux + useful error in case we are using AtomReact components on non atomReact app + remove some useless loggings for production usage
Do not throw error but log when AtomReact components are used inside non-atomreact app
Relaxed rules for context proptypes of AtomReact, to allow AtomReact components to be used in non-atomReact apps too
Allow to dispatch events during render phase (ie componentWillMount etc...)
allow createClass on AtomReact instead of createPureClass
